refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
boolimagegd resourceimage stringfilename
Outputs a GD image to the given filename.

&reftitle.parameters;



  &gd.image.description;

   filename



     The path to save the file to. If not set or &null;, the raw image stream
     will be outputted directly.

  &reftitle.examples;



    Outputting a GD image


<?php
// Create a blank image and add some text
$im = imagecreatetruecolor(120, 20);
$text_color = imagecolorallocate($im, 233, 14, 91);
imagestring($im, 1, 5, 5,  "A Simple Text String", $text_color);

// Output the image
imagegd($im);

// Free up memory
imagedestroy($im);
?>







    Saving a GD image


<?php
// Create a blank image and add some text
$im = imagecreatetruecolor(120, 20);
$text_color = imagecolorallocate($im, 233, 14, 91);
imagestring($im, 1, 5, 5,  "A Simple Text String", $text_color);

// Save the gd image
// The file format for GD images is .gd, see http://www.libgd.org/GdFileFormats
imagegd($im, 'simple.gd');

// Free up memory
imagedestroy($im);
?>

&reftitle.notes;



  The GD format is commonly used to allow fast loading of parts of images.
  Note that the GD format is only usable in GD-compatible applications.
